---
import Base from '../layouts/SectionLayout.astro';
---
<Base title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>Systems engineer working across security, AI inference, and RF. This site documents the projects, hardware, and logs.</p>

  <h2>Technical Background</h2>

  <h3>Areas of Focus</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Security:</strong> GPU-accelerated IDS, red-team simulations, adversarial networks</li>
    <li><strong>ML/AI:</strong> Local LLM inference, jailbreak eval, spiking neural networks</li>
    <li><strong>Hardware:</strong> PCIe passthrough, InfiniBand/RDMA, thermal management</li>
    <li><strong>RF:</strong> LEO satellite comms, SDR, antenna systems</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Tools & Stack</h3>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Languages:</em> Python, C/CUDA, Bash, Verilog</p>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Platforms:</em> Proxmox VE, CUDA, InfiniBand, llama.cpp, Linux KVM</p>
  <p class="tech-line"><em>Hardware:</em> Xeon E5-v3, Tesla P40, ConnectX-3, RTL-SDR</p>

  <h2>Current Work</h2>

  <p>Private AI inference lab on local hardware, LEO satellite ground station, and GPU-accelerated network defense — all built on the Hephaestus platform.</p>

  <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

  <div class="experience-list">
    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="phase-header">
        <span class="phase-locations">Digital Health Initiative</span>
        <span class="phase-date">2022–Present</span>
      </div>
      <p class="phase-role"><em>Startup Co-Founder · CTO</em></p>
      <ul class="bullets-circle">
        <li><strong>Funding:</strong> Secured $20,000 in early backing through investor pitches and technical demos.</li>
        <li><strong>Operations:</strong> Expanded the project toward a B2B model connecting Japanese and Chinese stakeholders.</li>
        <li><strong>Outreach:</strong> Collaborated with SDG communities at major Japanese universities, leading to NHK coverage and published press.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="phase-header">
        <span class="phase-locations">BGL</span>
        <span class="phase-date">2021–2023</span>
      </div>
      <p class="phase-role"><em>Import Export Manager · IT Specialist</em></p>
      <ul class="bullets-circle">
        <li><strong>Logistics Systems:</strong> Used NACCS workflows to keep customs handling compliant and reduce operational friction.</li>
        <li><strong>Internal Tooling:</strong> Built project management and shipment-tracking tools for import/export activity across partner logistics firms.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <div class="phase-header">
        <span class="phase-locations">University Research</span>
        <span class="phase-date">2023</span>
      </div>
      <p class="phase-role"><em>Artificial Intelligence Research Assistant</em></p>
      <ul class="bullets-circle">
        <li><strong>LLM Systems:</strong> Built a citation-aware PDF analysis application with LangChain, vector stores, and OpenAI APIs.</li>
        <li><strong>Computer Vision:</strong> Developed OCR and real-time detection pipelines for image classification and segmentation tasks.</li>
        <li><strong>Python Tooling:</strong> Created reusable machine learning utilities for parallel analysis workflows.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Timeline</h2>

  <div class="phase-timeline">

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 1 — Pre-University</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">
        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/jp.gif" alt="JP" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Tokyo</span>
            <span class="phase-date">2017–2022</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Independent Research</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>White-Hat Security:</strong> Completed penetration-testing and CTF course covering offensive-security tools and workflows.</li>
            <li><strong>VEX Robotics:</strong> Team Captain — C++ control systems, Fusion360 3D modelling, and mechanical design.</li>
            <li><strong>Institutional Grant:</strong> Only student-led personal technical project in the school to receive IT department funding for independent RF research.</li>
            <li><strong>SDR / ADS-B:</strong> RTL-SDR 1090 MHz demodulation for real-time airspace visualization via SDRAngel.</li>
            <li><strong>RF Research:</strong> Key-signal recognition and replay attacks; VEX-controller protocol vulnerability assessment.</li>
            <li><strong>Freelance:</strong> Illustrator, designer, and developer (2020–2022); Google Maps interface work at Google HQ Tokyo.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 2 — University</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">
        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/gb.gif" alt="GB" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Manchester</span>
            <span class="phase-date">2022–2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>University of Manchester — Computer Science</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>Final-Year Project:</strong> Independent implementation and extension of <em>CREST</em> SNN for DSEC-Detection. Initial SNN-only approach failed to converge — built custom diagnostic tools to inspect activations, then pivoted to a hybrid ANN→SNN weight transfer method to stabilise the model.</li>
            <li><strong>Himorogi OS:</strong> Minimal privacy-focused Linux environment.</li>
            <li><strong>Startup:</strong> Fitness/health-tech co-founder; collaborated with Japanese universities; NHK coverage.</li>
            <li><strong>Leadership:</strong> CS Dept Rep, PASS Leader, Engineering Ambassador, Language Society tutor, President of Manchester Japanese Society.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-sub">
          <p class="sub-header"><img src="/assets/flags/jp.gif" alt="JP" class="flag" /> Summer Deployments — Tokyo</p>

          <div class="phase-entry sub-entry">
            <div class="phase-header">
              <span class="phase-locations">Research & Dev</span>
              <span class="phase-date">Summer 2023</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="bullets-circle">
              <li><strong>BCI/EEG Research:</strong> Implemented Machine Learning classifiers for brain-computer interfaces (Python, Arduino).</li>
              <li><strong>Satellite Ops:</strong> Built custom antenna array for NOAA/Meteor satellite access via RTL-SDR.</li>
              <li><strong>LLM Dev:</strong> Built "PDF-QA" analysis tool (LangChain) and Live Flower Detection WebApp (YoloV8).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-entry sub-entry">
            <div class="phase-header">
              <span class="phase-locations">RF & Security</span>
              <span class="phase-date">Summer 2022</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="bullets-circle">
              <li><strong>RF Signal Research:</strong> IT-funded key-signal recognition and replay attacks.</li>
              <li><strong>Pentesting:</strong> VEX-controller protocol vulnerability assessment.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 3 — Post-Grad Circuit</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/gb.gif" alt="GB" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Manchester</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Jul 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Transition</em></p>
          <p class="phase-note">Closed the university phase — final conversations with professors and peers before the post-graduation circuit.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/gb.gif" alt="GB" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">London</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Jul–Aug 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Security Research & Consulting</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>Professional Circuit:</strong> Founder pitches, fintech discussions, hiring conversations, regulation panels, and security meetups.</li>
            <li><strong>Network Expansion:</strong> Met STEM students and professionals through Imperial College London circles — first post-university technical audience outside Manchester.</li>
            <li><strong>Freelance:</strong> Paid security audit on a live client-facing system ($400/hr).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/de.gif" alt="DE" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Berlin</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Aug–Sep 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Security Research</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>Security Culture:</strong> AI meetups, startup discussions, and hacker-adjacent technical spaces — adversarial systems, evasion logic, and anti-surveillance culture.</li>
            <li><strong>Research Pivot:</strong> Project direction shifted toward generative phishing shields and evasion-aware defensive systems.</li>
            <li><strong>c-base:</strong> Collaborated with local collectives including c-base.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 4 — Hardware Lab</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">
        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/jp.gif" alt="JP" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Tokyo</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Sep–Oct 2025</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Hephaestus Lab</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>BIOS Recovery:</strong> Motherboard arrived non-functional; revived via direct BIOS-chip clipping and hardware-level flash.</li>
            <li><strong>NIC Revival:</strong> Recovered soft-bricked quad-port NIC through hardware-level firmware flashing to support planned network experiments.</li>
            <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Built isolated Proxmox environments for InfiniBand, GPU-defense research, and red/blue-team workloads.</li>
            <li><strong>SDR / RF:</strong> Began satellite/RF branch — antenna testing, SDR signal capture, and early LEO satellite tracking.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 5 — Field Implementation</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/kh.gif" alt="KH" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Phnom Penh</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Oct 2025–Jan 2026</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Co-Founder — Digital Health Initiative</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>Digital Health:</strong> Applied neural-network and data-modelling techniques to injury prediction, performance analysis, and user-specific feedback with clinic-adjacent partners.</li>
            <li><strong>Adversarial Defense:</strong> Built prompt-shielding for medical data in a complex regulatory environment.</li>
            <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Lower-scaffolding environment — direct users, uneven data quality, and infrastructure limits as the field test condition.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-sub">
          <p class="sub-header"><img src="/assets/flags/th.gif" alt="TH" class="flag" /><img src="/assets/flags/sg.gif" alt="SG" class="flag" /><img src="/assets/flags/kh.gif" alt="KH" class="flag" /> Southeast Asia Circuit</p>

          <div class="phase-entry sub-entry">
            <div class="phase-header">
              <span class="phase-locations">Bangkok</span>
              <span class="phase-date">Dec 2025</span>
            </div>
            <p class="phase-note">Brief regional stop; comparative look at Bangkok's startup energy and visible development against the usual Southeast Asia framing.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-entry sub-entry">
            <div class="phase-header">
              <span class="phase-locations">Singapore</span>
              <span class="phase-date">Dec 2025</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="bullets-circle">
              <li><strong>Professional Checkpoint:</strong> Met an entrepreneur, investor, and advisor connected to Singapore and Dubai-facing circles; discussed startup direction and market movement.</li>
              <li><strong>Hackerspace:</strong> Presented projects at a Hackerspace/LeetCode meetup to software engineers outside the usual security-focused circle.</li>
              <li><strong>Security Culture:</strong> Met a China-based hardware/backend engineer with strict personal opsec practices.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="phase-entry sub-entry">
            <div class="phase-header">
              <span class="phase-locations">Phnom Penh</span>
              <span class="phase-date">Jan 2026</span>
            </div>
            <p class="phase-note">Returned briefly to continue digital health work and maintain momentum before the Tokyo build phase.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="phase">
      <div class="phase-divider"><span>Phase 6 — Build Phase</span></div>
      <div class="phase-entries">

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/jp.gif" alt="JP" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Tokyo</span>
            <span class="phase-date">Feb–May 2026</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Lab & Product Development</em></p>
          <ul class="bullets-circle">
            <li><strong>Full-Stack Dev:</strong> Continued co-founder development on the digital health/performance-tech initiative alongside selected design work.</li>
            <li><strong>Lab Systems:</strong> Infrastructure, security, local AI agents, and knowledge-system tooling using the operational Hephaestus platform.</li>
            <li><strong>SDR / LEO:</strong> Continued satellite/RF station work toward a complete SDR and LEO-tracking setup.</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Most of this phase documented through project logs on this site.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-entry">
          <div class="flag-row"><img src="/assets/flags/ca.gif" alt="CA" class="flag" /></div>
          <div class="phase-header">
            <span class="phase-locations">Vancouver</span>
            <span class="phase-date">May 2026–Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="phase-role"><em>Ongoing</em></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <h2>Contact & Links</h2>

  <p><strong>Resume:</strong> <a href="/resume.pdf">[PDF]</a></p>
  <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:kayraaraio@gmail.com">kayraaraio@gmail.com</a></p>
  <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kayra-arai-ozturk/">linkedin.com/in/kayra-arai-ozturk</a></p>
  <p><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/kiwaku">github.com/kiwaku</a></p>
  <p><strong>Legacy Portfolio:</strong> <a href="https://kiwaku.github.io/KayraAraiOzturk/">earlier work archive</a> <em>(not maintained)</em></p>

  <h2>Site Philosophy</h2>

  <p>Project documentation, build logs, and technical artifacts. Everything links back to source — diagrams, measurements, and code.</p>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Section spacing */
  h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5em;
    padding-top: 1em;
    border-top: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.5em;
    border-top: none;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-style: normal;
    margin-top: 1.2em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6em;
    color: #444;
  }

  .tech-line {
    margin: 0.25em 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .tech-line em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #666;
    min-width: 90px;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  /* Phase timeline */
  .phase-timeline {
    margin: 1.5em 0;
  }

  .experience-list {
    margin: 1.5em 0 2em 0;
  }

  .experience-item {
    margin-bottom: 1.4em;
    padding-left: 1em;
  }

  .experience-item:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .phase {
    margin-bottom: 2em;
  }

  .phase:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Phase divider — horizontal rule with label */
  .phase-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 1.2em;
  }

  .phase-divider::before,
  .phase-divider::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: #999;
  }

  .phase-divider span {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: bold;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #666;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* Phase entries */
  .phase-entries {
    padding-left: 1em;
  }

  .phase-entry {
    margin-bottom: 1.2em;
  }

  .phase-entry:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Header row: location + date */
  .phase-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1em;
    margin-bottom: 0.15em;
  }

  .phase-locations {
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .phase-date {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #888;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .phase-role {
    margin: 0 0 0.4em 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #555;
  }

  .phase-note {
    margin: 0.1em 0 0.4em 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #666;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Flag row — compact cluster above city names */
  .flag-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .flag-row .flag,
  .sub-header .flag {
    width: 16px;
    height: 11px;
    image-rendering: pixelated;
  }

  /* Bullet lists */
  .bullets-circle {
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .bullets-circle li {
    list-style-type: circle;
    margin-bottom: 0.2em;
  }

  /* Summer deployments sub-section */
  .phase-sub {
    margin-top: 1em;
    padding-top: 0.8em;
    padding-left: 1em;
    border-left: 1px dashed #ccc;
  }

  .sub-header {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: bold;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    margin: 0 0 0.8em 0;
  }

  .sub-entry {
    margin-bottom: 1em;
  }

  .sub-entry:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
